Our room was a good size - big, comfortable bed, ensuite shower room (small but newly refurbished).	Hotel staff were pleasant and helpful, the room was a decent size, with comfortable beds, tv, mini bar, and large shower room.	The only downside are the very small rooms, which do not leave much room for luggage, while the bathroom is fairly large with quite some unused space.	The room was smaller than American hotel rooms, but it was enough space for the two of us and the bathroom was bigger than average.	The sink/vanity unit was okay, and the towels were clean, fluffy and changed every day.